        "title": "Meeting &quot;java.sql.SQLException: Invalid column index&quot; when using jdbcTemplate to execute a SQL statement without argument.",
        "body": "<p>I have code like following:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class InspectDaoImpl extends JdbcDaoSupport{\n    ...\n    public ShiftTime getShiftTime(){\n        String sql = \"\";\n        ...//Only for assigning value to sql, it will be seen in exception stack trace. \n        Map&lt;String, Object&gt; map = this.getJdbcTemplate().queryForMap(sql, \"oracle\");//Error occured here. \n        ...\n    }\n    ...\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When I call this method, it post an error as <code>java.sql.SQLException: Invalid column index<\/code>. <br>\nThe main stack trace is this, it includes my SQL statement: <\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Caused by: org.springframework.jdbc.InvalidResultSetAccessException: PreparedStatementCallback; invalid ResultSet access for SQL [<br>\n                  <strong>SELECT * FROM <br>\n                  (SELECT * FROM shifttime ORDER BY id DESC)<br>\n                  WHERE rownum = 1<\/strong><br>\n          ]; nested exception is java.sql.SQLException: Invalid column index<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>I have search of this exception, but those conditions are all different from my case. <\/p>\n\n<p>There isn't any placeholder like \"?\" in my SQL statement, so why can this error occur? <\/p>\n",
